31 industrial purposes, or any other purpose that is not primarily residential;

14 SENATE BILL 150
1 (ii) Improved or to be improved by any apartment, condominium,
2 cooperative, or other building for multifamily use of greater than four dwelling units; or
3 (iii) Leased for dwellings or mobile homes that are erected or placed
4 in a mobile home development or mobile home park.
5 (2) This section does not apply to residential property that is or was used,
6 intended to be used, or authorized to be used for four or fewer dwelling units.
7 (b) (1) Whenever, in a case that involves a 99–year ground lease renewable
8 forever, at least 6 months ground rent is in arrears and the landlord has the lawful right
9 to reenter for the nonpayment of the rent, the landlord, no less than 45 days after sending
10 to the tenant by certified mail, return receipt requested, at the tenant’s last known address,
11 and also by first–class mail to the title agent or attorney listed on the deed to the property
12 or the intake sheet recorded with the deed, a bill for the ground rent due, may bring an
13 action for possession of the property under § 14–108.1 of this article[; if].
14 (2) (I) IF the tenant cannot be personally served IN ACCORDANCE
15 WITH PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION, or there is no tenant in actual possession
16 of the property, service by posting notice on the property may be made in accordance with
17 the Maryland Rules.
18 (II) Personal service or posting in accordance with the Maryland
19 Rules shall stand in the place of a demand and reentry.
20 (c) (1) Before entry of a judgment the landlord shall give written notice of the
21 pending entry of judgment to each mortgagee of the lease, or any part of the lease, who
22 before entry of the judgment has recorded in the land records of each county where the
23 property is located a timely request for notice of judgment.
24 (2) A request for notice of judgment DESCRIBED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)
25 OF THIS SUBSECTION shall:
26 (i) Be recorded in a separate [docket or book] PAPER OR
27 ELECTRONIC INDEX that is indexed under the name of the mortgagor;
28 (ii) Identify the property on which the mortgage is held and refer to
29 the date and recording reference of that mortgage;
30 (iii) State the name and address of the holder of the mortgage; and
31 (iv) Identify the ground lease by stating:
32 1. The name of the original lessor;
33 2. The date the ground lease was recorded; and

